                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus from="35vb" to="36rc">ff. 35vb-36rc</locus>
                           <desc type="GuestText">Tarik za-taṣǝḥfa ba-mawāʿǝlihomu la-naguśa nagaśt Yoḥannǝs...,
                              "History that was written in the time of the King of Kings
                              Yoḥannǝs...", a short historiographic composition. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ተሪክ፡ ዘተጽሕፈ፡ በመዋዕሊሆሙ፡ ለነጉሠ፡ ነገሥት፡ ዮሐንስ፡</q>
                           <note>The note, in a mediocre hand, was written during
                           the time of King Yoḥannǝs IV (r. <date>1872-1889</date>), nǝbura ʾǝd ʾIyāsu and ʾabbā
                           Takla Hāymānot and ʾalaqā Takla ʾƎsṭifānos from Gondar (the scribe?) "who
                           was with them". The note is a list of metropolitans of the Ethiopian
                           Orthodox Church from ʾabbā Salāma to ʾabuna ʾAtnātewos (in tenure
                           1867-76), with description of some events. It contains 107 names.
                           Besides, it mentions some rulers of Ethiopia and events that took place
                           when they were in power, such as King Susǝnyos and the arrival of the
                           Catholic priests, the restoration of the Orthodox faith, the rule of King
                           ʾIyasu, the conflict between daǧǧāzmāč Wube and rās ʿAli, the death
                           of ʾAtnatewos at ʿAdwā. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#181r">f. 181rb-rc</locus>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">Extensive donation note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                            <note>The note is written in the main hand. It states
                           that the commissioner of the Ms. is ʾabbā Gǝrmā Ṣǝyon who donated
                              it to the Dabra Dāmmo monastery. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>The title ስንክሳር and the internal number of the monastic
                           library (384) are written on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.  </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc>Shelfmark C3-IV-265 is given on <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>.  </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc>Four
                           lines of the incipit of the Synaxarion are written four times on <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>.</desc></item>
                     </list>
                     
                    
                  </additions>
