                  <provenance>Gǝrmā Ṣǝyon is mentioned as the commissioner
                     of the Ms. in the postscript and in Additio 2. His name and the names of other
                     individuals are written in supplication formulas throughout the Ms.: Gǝrmā
                     Ṣǝyon (e.g., <locus target="#3vb">3vb</locus>, 4va, 46ra, 66rb, 90ra, 106rc,
                     146va, 170rc), his father Labāse Krǝstos (e.g., <locus target="#5vc">5vc</locus>, 7rb, 47ra, 66rb, 90ra, 106rb, 146va), Walda Krǝstos (e.g.,
                     <locus target="#3ra">3ra</locus>, 3vab), ʾabuna ʾAskalā Māryām (e.g., <locus target="#171vb">171vb</locus>, 172rac, 173ra), ʾabuna
